defaultA particular focus of the analysis that CESI carried out on behalf of the LGA was an understanding of the local impacts of reforms that
default are most likely to affect households’ ability to remain in or to afford housing – particularly in households where no one works.  The report focused on the local impacts of reforms affecting Housing Benefit, and specifically the impacts of:
